:INFO
Bottling and Carbonating Safely
Use plastic bottles or flip-top glass bottles designed for carbonated drinks. Fill \
leaving 3 to 5 centimeters of headspace. Seal tightly. Store at room temperature for one \
to three days, squeezing plastic bottles to gauge pressure. When a plastic bottle

:NOTE
Bottle Safety and Avoiding Explosions
Over-carbonated bottles can burst. This risk is real with glass bottles. \
If using glass, open one test bottle each day during secondary fermentation \
to check pressure before it builds to dangerous levels. \
In warm weather, carbonation happens in 12 to 24 hours rather than two to three days. \
When in doubt, refrigerate early. You can always let it sit at room temperature \
for another few hours after chilling if it needs more fizz.

